register.description: The Controller Config 2 Register contains various fields to control the configuration ports on the Host Controller. This register sets the LSB fields in the register inside the Host Controller.

bitfield.description: Slot Type Should be set based on the final product usage.
Asynchronous Interrupt Support Suggested Value is 1h (The Core supports monitoring of Asynchronous Interrupt).
1.8 V Support Suggested Value is 1h (The 1.8 Volt Switching is supported by Core).
3.0 V Support Should be set based on whether 3.0 V is supported on the SD Interface.
3.3 V Support Suggested Value is 1h as the 3.3 V is the default voltage on the SD Interface.
Suspend/Resume Support Suggested Value is 1h (The Suspend/Resume is supported by Core).
SDMA Support Suggested Value is 1h (The SDMA is supported by Core).
High Speed Support Suggested Value is 1h (The High Speed mode is supported by Core).
ADMA2 Support Suggested Value is 1h (The ADMA2 is supported by Core).
8-bit Support for Embedded Device Suggested Value is 1h (The Core supports 8-bit Interface).
Max Block Length Maximum Block Length supported by the Core/Device.
Base Clock Frequency for SD Clock This is the frequency of the xin_clk.
Timeout Clock Unit Suggested Value is 0h (KHz).
Timeout Clock Frequency Suggested Value is 1 KHz.

register.description: The Controller Config 3 Register contains various fields to control the configuration ports on the Host Controller. This register sets the MSB fields in the register inside the Host Controller.

bitfield.description: 1.8 V VDD2 Support
ADMA3 Support
Clock Multiplier This field indicates clock multiplier value of programmable clock generator.
Re-Tuning Modes Should be set to 0h as the Core supports only the Software Timer based Re-Tuning.
Use Tuning for SDR50 This bit should be set if the application wants Tuning be used for SDR50 Modes.
Timer Count for Re-Tuning This is the Timer Count for Re-Tuning Timer for Re-Tuning Mode 1 to 3.
Driver Type 4 Support This bit should be set based on whether Driver Type 4 for 1.8 Signalling is supported or not.
Driver Type D Support This bit should be set based on whether Driver Type D for 1.8 Signalling is supported or not.
Driver Type C Support This bit should be set based on whether Driver Type C for 1.8 Signalling is supported or not.
Driver Type A Support This bit should be set based on whether Driver Type A for 1.8 Signalling is supported or not.
DDR50 Support Suggested Value is 1h (The Core supports DDR50 mode of operation).
SDR104 Support.
SDR50 Support.
